    "Considerations": [
        "During scheduled system maintenance or updates, legitimate changes to the registry may occur, including modifications to the Local Port Monitor settings. These changes can trigger false alerts.",
        "When new software or drivers are installed, they may modify registry settings related to the Local Port Monitor. This legitimate activity can be mistaken for malicious behavior, resulting in a false positive alert.",
        "Changes in printer configurations, such as adding or removing printers, can lead to modifications in the registry under the Local Port Monitor keys. These legitimate changes can trigger false alerts if not properly accounted for."
